    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 150 species in two families including ducks, geese, and swans. Characteriezed as web-footed birds with broad bills containing fine plates or lamellae (except for screamers) and large-footed marsh birds with chickenlike bills.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
